<subSubSection id="D9F16554FF9CBA30BC1BF66CBA5BFD5E" pageId="32" pageNumber="651" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="915436DFFF9CBA30BC1BF66CBA5BFD5E" blockId="32.[2054,2648,268,695]" pageId="32" pageNumber="651">
<taxonomicName id="56EB4D5CFF9CBA30BC1BF66CBB36FEE3" authorityName="G. S. Miller" authorityYear="1902" box="[2057,2320,268,301]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Chaerephon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="651" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="jobensis">Chaerephon jobensis</taxonomicName>
has sometimes been considered to include 
<taxonomicName id="56EB4D5CFF9CBA30BD75F654B828FE9B" authorityName="Troughton" authorityYear="1931" box="[2407,2574,308,341]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Chaerephon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="651" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="solomonis">C. solomonis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="56EB4D5CFF9CBA30BC1BF63BBA82FEB2" authorityName="Felten" authorityYear="1964" box="[2057,2212,347,380]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Chaerephon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="651" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bregullae">C. bregullae</taxonomicName>
as subspecies but genetic research by S. Ingleby and D. Colgan in 2003 has demonstrated them to be distinct species. Race colonicus was not recognized as distinct by W. D. L. Ride in 1970, but was reinstated as a subspecies by Ingleby and Colgan in 2003. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
